Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.53,0:00:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will kill all my enemies...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.46,0:00:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they happen to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.34,0:00:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.74,0:02:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty, though the\Ndelays are quite regrettable,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.36,0:02:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we are still relieved to hear\Nthat the Hero is on his way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.70,0:02:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I hear that the demons\Nare becoming more active as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.21,0:02:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will be needing the Hero's powers soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.75,0:02:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong, Princess Liliana?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.67,0:02:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem ill at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, Pope Ishtar, I'm fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kouki-{\i1}san {\i0}and the others were summoned\Nto our world by an act of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.98,0:03:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hero has returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.28,0:03:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were summoned to\Nprotect us humans from the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a way to go back\Nto their original world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kouki-{\i1}san {\i0}and the others had\Nno choice but to obey the will of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.42,0:03:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A horrible accident happened during\Ntheir training to prepare for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.38,0:03:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No more...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.51,0:03:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lily!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuku!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.03,0:04:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried by how long it took you\Nto return from the Great Orcus Labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.45,0:04:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're fine. How about everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.87,0:04:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Second Party members\Nwere all training hard every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.13,0:04:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We can't just sit idly by and rely\Non Kouki and the others all the time."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.72,0:04:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We have to be strong too."\NThat's what they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.48,0:04:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Eririn, want something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.06,0:04:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eririn?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.44,0:04:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, let's drink something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.36,0:04:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuku, if you didn't return,\Nthey said they would go out to find you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.74,0:04:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They truly care about their friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.46,0:04:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.17,0:04:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you in such a bad mood?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.08,0:04:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were the monsters you saw\Ndown there really that bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.63,0:05:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the monsters... It's him.\NHe's worse than the monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.63,0:05:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kousuke! Where are you, Kousuke! Kousuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.01,0:05:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you've mentioned it,\Nyes, Kousuke is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.72,0:05:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kousuke! Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.77,0:05:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Kousuke!\N--Kousuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.56,0:05:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really do blend in with\Nthe background, as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.78,0:05:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I cry now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.32,0:05:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I worried you. I'm glad\Nto see everyone's in good spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.99,0:05:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.33,0:05:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Kaori?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.41,0:05:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lily, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.96,0:05:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.42,0:05:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Kaori is with Nagumo-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.17,0:05:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.51,0:05:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that why Kouki-{\i1}san {\i0}seems so out of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's probably part of it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.85,0:05:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun {\i0}ended up\Nsaving Kouki again, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.89,0:05:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.19,0:06:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That said, he is "The Hero" after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.19,0:06:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't let him stay sad for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.78,0:06:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.15,0:06:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it comes down to it, I'll handle him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.49,0:06:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm truly glad to hear Nagumo-{\i1}san {\i0}is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.49,0:06:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been best\Nif he could come back with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.25,0:06:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he said he's searching for another\Nway for us to go back to our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.79,0:06:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a little disappointed\Nthat I couldn't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.38,0:06:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd be surprised if you did. He looks\Ntotally different, among other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.76,0:06:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By now, I'm sure he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.69,0:06:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite terrible outside, Tio-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it wasn't for Hajime-{\i1}san{\i0}'s Brise,\Nwe would have been in a lot of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.90,0:06:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, Shea. This is not a place\NI'd enter if I had any other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.33,0:06:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so different from\Nthe last time I was here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.08,0:07:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so cool, and my eyes don't hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.79,0:07:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa is so awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Papa Hajime is awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.05,0:07:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want some cold water, Myu-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.17,0:07:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do! Thank you, Big Sister Kaori!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.84,0:07:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shirasaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.31,0:07:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kaori, please stop calling me\N"Papa Hajime." It feels weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.56,0:07:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But that's what Myu-{\i1}chan{\i0}\Ncalls you, and you don't seem to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.02,0:07:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay when Myu says it.\NHaving a classmate call me that, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.74,0:07:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to say, is uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.65,0:07:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Well then, I won't say it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.41,0:07:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But one day, when I have a baby, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.91,0:07:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.16,0:07:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a previous engagement,\Nalready promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Introduction to his parents,\Nalready promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our happy family life plans are all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.30,0:07:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We also have plans to go on\Na date in Hajime's hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.06,0:08:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's so much that I know\Nabout Hajime-{\i1}kun {\i0}that you don't, Yue!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.48,0:08:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like his future aspirations,\Nhis hobbies...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.73,0:08:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yue, do you know about Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s\Nfavorite anime and manga?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... That doesn't matter now.\NThose things don't exist here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.95,0:08:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Can't you see that Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}\Nlooks like an anime character now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His weapons, too. That new one\Nhe's making... The Cross Bit, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.91,0:08:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's totally based on the Funnel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kaori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.63,0:08:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you act like you've won
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.13,0:08:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without knowing anything\Nabout the things he loves?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bold words, Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.64,0:08:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll tell you about\Nwhat Hajime loves...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.56,0:08:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to do, in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.48,0:08:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-B-B-B-Bed?! So, you've already...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.23,0:08:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, let that sink in, how far ahead I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.65,0:08:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Sister Yue and Big Sister Kaori\Nare always fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.99,0:09:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like it when the big sisters\Naren't nice to each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.37,0:09:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you ashamed of behaving\Nlike that in front of Myu-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.08,0:09:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's bad for her education.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please restrain yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.75,0:09:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How regrettable, for Shea to scold me\Nand actually have a good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.71,0:09:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Myu-{\i1}chan{\i0}, Shea...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.93,0:09:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master, there seems to be\Na disturbance up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.64,0:09:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are sand worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.15,0:09:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sand worms in the Gruen Desert\Nare very common, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.15,0:09:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.65,0:09:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like they can't decided\Nwhether or not they should eat their prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.62,0:09:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's how it appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.37,0:09:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They eat anything, I don't think\Nthey'd ever hesitate in front of a meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.47,0:10:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, pervert! Get your breasts off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.87,0:10:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kaori!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.21,0:10:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You of all people, what are\Nyou doing in this situation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.34,0:10:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous! The danger is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.26,0:10:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm clinging on because\Nthe dangerous danger is right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.34,0:10:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you Kaori, a surprise attack\Nto get ahead of me? Well played.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.35,0:10:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I had the purest of intentions!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to see\Nwhat it felt like to be clingy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.10,0:10:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And also, if possible, to enjoy Hajime?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.11,0:10:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, correct... Wait, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.23,0:10:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't phrase it like that!\NI'm not a lewd person like you, Yue!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.28,0:11:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You call me lewd? Well, I can't deny\Nthat I am, when I'm alone with Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.07,0:11:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you two just shut up for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Yue, no more "nighttime" talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.37,0:11:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're running backwards!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.25,0:11:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa Hajime is such a good driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.96,0:11:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said stop calling me Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.59,0:11:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime, I want babies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Save the fun for the inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will there be fun for me, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.09,0:11:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll throw you out into the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.43,0:11:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so harsh to only me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.14,0:11:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, this is\Nthe first time I've used this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.15,0:11:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know Brise\Nhad something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime, you're a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.94,0:11:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master is truly great.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.75,0:11:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.71,0:11:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure Myu doesn't see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.50,0:11:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's find out what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.80,0:12:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're looking at us.\NIs that bad, Hajime-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There seems to be a much bigger crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.60,0:12:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.50,0:12:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.88,0:12:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A person?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.46,0:12:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that what the sand worms were after?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.96,0:12:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}, would it be\Nall right to go over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we do have Myu-{\i1}chan {\i0}with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.85,0:12:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It would be very risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.26,0:12:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Myu is fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.14,0:12:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess, as a Priest,\Nyou want to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.73,0:12:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.73,0:13:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Myu, stay in Brise with Shea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.07,0:13:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.57,0:13:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious to know\Nwhy he didn't get eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.37,0:13:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.63,0:13:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}"Status: Overloaded mana,\Nunable to release mana"{\an}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.51,0:13:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A mana overload?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.09,0:13:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some sort of ingested poison is causing\Nthis person's mana to go berserk?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.97,0:13:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, what did you find?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.35,0:13:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not certain, but it seems\Nlike he ingested something
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.85,0:13:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's causing a state of "mana overload."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mana overload?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's unable to release the extra mana,\Nso the forced overload coming from inside
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is causing pressure on the body,\Nwhich can't handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.82,0:13:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't do something,\Nhis organs and veins will rupture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.45,0:13:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heaven's blessing,\NI hereby request recurrence...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:13:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consecration!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.25,0:14:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It had no effect. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.05,0:14:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it can't be cleansed, is it that\Ndeeply dissolved into his body...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.35,0:14:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May the grace of light bless you\Nin this holy sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.02,0:14:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No evil shall pass\Nso long as I hold the gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.07,0:14:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sanctorum!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.15,0:14:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High-rank light magic, "Sanctorum."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.03,0:14:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It allows the caster to transfer mana\Nfrom one person to another,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.24,0:14:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to prevent mana depletion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.41,0:14:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can also be used to forcefully\Ndrain mana from someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.42,0:14:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess she's using it to drain out\Nthe overloaded mana from this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.88,0:14:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the drained mana goes into\Nthe Holy Crystal ring I gave her. I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.28,0:15:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he's in\Nimmediate danger anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the root cause\Nhasn't been resolved yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.41,0:15:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I drain too much of his mana,\Nhe might die from emaciation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.79,0:15:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I've only drained\Nenough to ease the pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.71,0:15:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, he's still...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.96,0:15:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we do something,\Nhe'll go into mana overload again,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.63,0:15:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the fatigue could\Ncause him to weaken and die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.88,0:15:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen symptoms\Nlike these in anything I've studied.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.97,0:15:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yue, Tio, do you have any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.31,0:15:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.35,0:15:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.39,0:15:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case, do a diagnosis on us, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.61,0:15:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is an unknown disease,\Nit could be airborne.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A goddess?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.29,0:16:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.... I must have died,\Nand I'm going to meet God...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.88,0:16:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear goddess...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.59,0:16:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.43,0:16:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop spewing nonsense and get up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.97,0:16:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.35,0:16:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was done for, but it\Nseems God has not forsaken me yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.44,0:16:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}, maybe we\Nshould bring him inside the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's way too hot out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not hot... Where am I?\NIs this a divine sanctuary?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.12,0:16:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.12,0:16:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.84,0:16:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.13,0:16:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, thank you\Nfor saving my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had died out there,\Neverything would have been over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.18,0:17:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Bize Feuward Zengen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.98,0:17:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the son of the duke, Lanzwi Feuward\NZengen, of the Dukedom of Ankaji.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.40,0:17:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dukedom of Ankaji?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.27,0:17:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The important trade hub for\Nthe seafood coming out of Erisen,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.36,0:17:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the city on the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.15,0:17:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Erisen is where\NMyu was born and raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.61,0:17:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mama is waiting for me there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.87,0:17:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master, Ankaji is the town\Nwe were headed towards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.67,0:17:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that town is in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.21,0:17:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us about what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A few days ago, the citizens of Ankaji\Nbegan to collapse from fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.68,0:17:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A poison that causes mana overload\Nwas found in our drinking water...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.64,0:17:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our oasis was polluted by this substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.10,0:17:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The oasis is protected, maintained,\Nand managed with the utmost care.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.90,0:17:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did this poison get in the oasis?\NWho could have done this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.94,0:17:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a cure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:17:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It involves a special\Nmineral called Stillstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.41,0:18:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stillstone has the effect of calming\Na person's mana when ingested.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.41,0:18:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a precious mineral, mined in\Nsmall amounts in the Gruen Volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.87,0:18:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Gruen Volcano? That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.13,0:18:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the adventurers\Nof Ankaji have all fallen ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.71,0:18:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The average adventurer\Nwouldn't even be able
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to get past the sandstorm\Nsurrounding the volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.80,0:18:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if a powerful\Nadventurer was available,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,seeing how we're almost out\Nof safe drinking water...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.93,0:18:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in a nutshell, you set out to call\Nfor help, but you also collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so Ankaji is in really deep trouble now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.15,0:18:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone needs to cleanse the oasis
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.53,0:18:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and bring Stillstone\Nfrom the volcano, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.28,0:18:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! You are Gold-ranked adventurers,\Nand you are a goddess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.91,0:18:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This must truly be God's will!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must have sent these\Ngoddesses to save us, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.17,0:18:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.96,0:18:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to officially ask you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.26,0:19:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a deputy of the Duke of Ankaji,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.05,0:19:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,please, lend us aid!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.36,0:19:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.86,0:19:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to save them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Myu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.82,0:19:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we were going\Nto stop by Ankaji, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.20,0:19:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.79,0:19:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to get busy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.25,0:19:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.17,0:19:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.25,0:19:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We want you to go directly to\Nthe volcano to mine the Stillstone,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.05,0:19:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but perhaps it is best to first travel\Nto the royal capital to get water--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.30,0:19:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need\Nto go to the royal capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.18,0:19:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be able to get water.\NWe're heading to Ankaji right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.35,0:19:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should be able to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.98,0:19:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Yue?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.52,0:19:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.98,0:19:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you stop melting away\Ninto a world of your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.36,0:20:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right? It's always\Njust the two of them. Not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.92,0:20:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,General Freid! Is it true\Nthat Cattleya was defeated?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.34,0:20:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikhail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be true!\NCattleya could not have died!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.97,0:20:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had so many monsters\Nby her side, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.43,0:20:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mission at the\Ntown of Ur was also a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.15,0:20:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ur, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The operations were partially successful.\NSixty thousand monsters were recruited
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.94,0:20:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and were about to lay waste to\Nthe town and kill the Fertility Goddess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.49,0:20:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But an "Irregular" crushed our plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.41,0:20:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An "Irregular"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.12,0:20:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just four individuals wiped out\Nthe entire monster army.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reiss, who was on the mission,\Nlost an arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.25,0:20:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible. Reiss, too...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.79,0:21:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The four Irregulars left Ur and went\Nstraight to the Great Orcus Labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when Cattleya was\Nabout to encounter the Hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.51,0:21:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So these Irregulars killed Cattleya...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.76,0:21:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our enemies are stronger\Nthan we anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will head to the volcano now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must acquire a new Age of God magic\Nand grow stronger. At any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.94,0:21:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,General Freid...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.48,0:21:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All in service to our king\Nand for the God we worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.70,0:21:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikhail, defend our home while\NI am away. War is coming, soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.12,0:21:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will avenge Cattleya's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.04,0:21:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have crushed the sacred mission\Ngiven to me by my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.55,0:21:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will pay dearly for that,\Nmy unseen enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.14,0:21:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment you see me is\Nthe last moment of your lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.81,0:21:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no place on\Nthis world for heathens
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.81,0:21:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or Irregulars.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.95,0:23:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode, "Burning Light."